  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      Patients with inoperable Non-Small-Cell Lung Cancer will receive thoracic radiation therapy
      66 Gy over 33 fractions,and concurrent with 2 cycles of chemotherapy with pemetrexed (500
      mg/m2,d1,repeated every 3 weeks)and carboplatin (AUC=5,d1,repeated every 3 weeks).
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
